content.description: Start on top of the small slab/block.  Move up to the break then traverse out right along the break to the arete, and top out.
content.location: From the catacomb, continue walking south down the other side of the small hill.  You should pass two or three smaller boulders on your left, and after maybe 100 yards you'll see this boulder. Pot Kettle Black is on the north face.

content.description: Starts the same as for Pot Kettle Black, but instead of traversing right, continue straight up.
content.location: From the catacomb, continue walking south down the other side of the small hill.  You should pass two or three smaller boulders on your left, and after maybe 100 yards you'll see this boulder.   Jurassic Park is on the North Face.

content.description: Climbs up the arete on the south face.
content.location: From the catacomb, continue walking south down the other side of the small hill.  You should pass two or three smaller boulders on your left, and after maybe 100 yards you'll see this boulder.   Nobody You Know is on the south face.

content.description: Climbs up just left of the arete.  Start low on a good hold, move up the crack to the horn, and top out straight up.
content.location: From the catacomb, continue walking south down the other side of the small hill.  You should pass two or three smaller boulders on your left, and after maybe 100 yards you'll see this boulder. Coffin Varnish is on the east face.

content.description: Climbs the face just right of Nobody You Know.  Start in the horizontal break, and go straight up.
content.location: From the catacomb, continue walking south down the other side of the small hill.  You should pass two or three smaller boulders on your left, and after maybe 100 yards you'll see this boulder.  Birds Of Prey is on the south face.

content.description: An isolated boulder, sitting like a stump on a faintly defined ridge.
